JavaScript is a scripting or programming language that enables you to introduce complex features on 
web pages. If a web page does more than just sit down and display static information it allows you to 
access timely content changes, interactive charts, animated 2D/3D graphics , video jukebox scrolling, 
etc. This is the third layer of traditional web-technology layer cake, two of which (HTML and CSS)

HTML is the markup language we use for structuring and giving context to our web content, such as 
specifying paragraphs, headings and data tables, or embedding images and videos in the website.

CSS is a language of style rules that we use to add styling to our HTML content, such as setting 
background colors and fonts, and multi-column layout of our content.